rComments: He's super nice and the course was really interesting, but also really challenging. There was way more scientific math involved than I'd hoped for. (I took this course for my science distribution credit.)

drop this class immediatly, the ta's are terrible, make many mistakes. i showed up to every lecture read the whole textbook and still did bab, hes a nice man tho, passionate yet monotone, if you take his class i would suggest waiting till you get your grade back than decide, for non scince students its quite unreasonable
good teacher, but course content heavy, 3 classes a week of just content lol if you don't keep up you're screwed. Difficult course for me.

Prof Lester is an incredible professor, passionate about astrology. He is quite monotone and his notes are inclusive so lectures aren't really necessary. Best way to do well is to go to his office with any questions and concerns, he's an excellent teacher. Won't find answers to problem sets online but he will put in the time to explain.

Really easy class, but often gets boring and dull. The assignments are free marks, and the tests and exam wasn't too bad either. Make sure you write every single detail on his short answer questions; he's very picky regarding those. But hey, if you every wanna touch a meteorite, then this class is perfect just for you :)

Took AST 101 and the course is designed for student's who don't have a science background. A better Astronomer than lecturer; his styling of teaching can be boring. Attending class is an easy way to get a good grade. Getting the textbook isn't mandatory but many of his test questions are based off the book and homework load isn't too heavy.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Certainly a better Astronomer than a teacher, but his experience and knowledge of the field makes him an excellent mouthpiece for the industry. He seems to prefer being one on one with students than teaching in lecture halls, so office visits are a good idea. He is very understanding of the student perspective, so his homework/tests are fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lots of homework']

rComments: I'm not a science student and was overwhelmed by the amount of preconceived knowledge that was expected. I found his lecture style boring and monotonous so I disliked going to lecture (But I did or else I would have failed).  If you're good at physics, this class will be a breeze. But non-science majors looking for a science credit, be warned.

AST101 was an interesting class in my opinion. The professor was clear in his lectures, and the tests were fair game. As long as you read the textbook and show up to class and take notes you should do good in this course.
John Lester is by far one of my favourite professors at Universitt of Toronto. The course was really interesting I highly reccomend taking one of his classes.
His tests and homework are pretty tricky, some questions aren't even answered in the textbook
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Prof. Lester is probably one of my favourite's at UTM (and it's not because he wears bow-ties every day). This course is very interesting & he is very knowledgeable! Midterms were super easy (in my pov) and I got 10/10 on the homework assignments (GOOGLE and Cosmic Calc. is your friend!). Feel free to talk or email him, he is very helpful! :)

Not a good prof. A lot of science for non-science course, wasnt bothed by the fact that the whole class failed both tests always blamed us but didnt change the way tests were done. If good at physics and chem then take this course otherwise avoid.

Was not the best prof. its a non-science course but put on a lot of science type questions on  homework assignments and somewhat on tests. Also whole class failed tests and wasnt super bothered by that wasnt always clear in lecture took most stuff from textbook just look at the pictures and pay attention in lectures and should get a decent grade

AWESOME PROF. Very approachablenice. NOT condescendingarrogantintimidating  AT ALL. Ask for help; likes to help students. Testsdifficult but if you READ textbook+UNDERSTAND concepts, you will do well. Lecturesvery clear+helpful+updates about recent space activity+easy to followunderstand; GO TO LECTURES. Bonus points for the bow tie.
Great Prof, always there to help
one of the best professors ive met

Favourite Prof! Very helpful, not intimidating. Attend the lectures-very important! Ditch the textbook. And yeah, tests are not textbook stuff either. Cannot google assignments 'cause he comes up with the questions! Tests were damn hard and pretty tricky. If u know the material, you can pass. Make use of office hours (8am to 6pm). Loved the course.
Make sure you go to the lectures, write everything down, understand rather than memorize (though the latter is also required), and genreally study and keep up. Otherwise, you'll have problems
Very good prof, knows the material explains everything well. the course is very interesting but the tests are extremely difficult

Class lectures are somewhat dull, but he certainly knows his material. Kinda of felt dumb asking for help understanding the physics/math aspect of the course, he was not really helpful-made me feel worse actually. Love the bow tie.
Class average 33%, nuff said :(
Really nice prof, but makes his tests very tricky. Make sure you thoroughly understand the concepts and know how to apply them to diff situations. Always ask him for help, he likes helping students.

Everyone failed the midterm - Lester didn't find anything wrong with this. Everyone had to drop his course. Utterly useless professor - no control over his TA's and their marking. Lester has officially killed my love for Astronomy.

Very nice and smart guy that is willing to help you learn. He makes his tests very tricky though watch out. Not only do you have to know the material but you also have to apply it in unfimilar situations on tests.

I thought this class would be bird course, but apparently not anymore :( i read and followed the review on this website, but i think his reputation is going down, cuz everyone think its a bird course.... watch out for him, he ain't easy anymore :( fml

This was the first year without a lab in this class. He made the course content seem easy in the lecture, but I felt like he tried too hard to make it complicated during the tests. Overall, he's an ineffective teacher. No lie, it's pretty bad when both midterms averaged a class fail...

He was a really nice guy and the lecture topics were easy to understand and clearly communicated.  Watch out for the tests though... you have to APPLY the concepts discussed in class and it gets tricky.  Make sure you understand all the questions on the last year's tests which he posts on the website.

gotta love the bowtie! seems like he'll be boring at first, but he isn't. hes very intelligent, and great at explaining concepts. he uses diagrams and pictures to help the students grasp things. labs were mostly group work. also provided us with an update of current space events and when they would be. he has lots of experience and very interesting
easy class! just copy down his notes with a few of ur own foot notes and ull be fine. boring in lectures but he's a good guy

Very knowledgable and overall very clear. Though his lectures can get somewhat boring. His assignments and tutorial assignments are generally easy as long as you know what to pick for your research topics.
good guy
